 r‚Üź{performChecks}CloseProject projects;list;project;ind;res;list;closed;buff
‚ćĚ Breaks the Link between a project and its folder on disk, and potentially executes a check functon afterwards.
‚ćĚ In case ‚ćĶ is empty, ALL projects are closed.
‚ćĚ `projects` may be one of:
‚ćĚ 1. Empty vector (=close all)
‚ćĚ 2. One or more project names like `#.Foo`
‚ćĚ 3. One or more alias names like `[my-alias]`
‚ćĚ 4. One or more paths of currently open projects
‚ćĚ 5. A mixture of 2, 3 and 4
‚ćĚ `performChecks` can be a Boolean that defaults to 1, meaning "perform checks, if any".
‚ćĚ See "CheckForDropboxConflicts" as an example.
‚ćĚ A 0 as left argument would therefore prevent such checks from being performed.\\
‚ćĚ Returns the number of projects closed.
 r‚Üź0
 performChecks‚Üź{0<‚éēNC ‚ćĶ:‚ćé‚ćĶ ‚čĄ 1}'performChecks'
 list‚ÜźListOpenProjects 1
